The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Oct. 16: Private lender Axis Bank today announced the reorganisation of its operations into four strategic business units  retail banking (SME and agri), corporate, non-banking retail subsidiaries and corporate centre. Retail banking will be headed by S.K. Chakrabarti, who will be designated as the executive director.                            
	 Mumbai, Oct. 16: Market regulator Sebi today said trade in corporate bonds would have to be routed through clearing corporations from December 1, a move that analysts say would check factors that aggravated financial crisis.                            
	 Singapore, Oct. 16: High savings rate and a domestic expenditure-driven economy helped India mitigate the adverse impact of the financial meltdown, the RBI has said.                            
	 New York, Oct. 16: The Bank of America (BoA) has suffered a third-quarter loss of $1 billion as it continues to grapple with rising credit costs. BoA had raked in a profit of $1.2 billion in the corresponding period a year ago.                                                                                                                           
